    <h2 class="text-center">About Computer History</h2>
    <p>
      The history of computers spans thousands of years, from the abacus and mechanical devices to today’s powerful
      digital machines. Key breakthroughs include the Turing Machine concept, early electronic computers like ENIAC, and
      the microprocessor revolution. The internet and smartphones in the 1990s and 2000s transformed how we live, work,
      and connect with the world.
    </p>
